|CK0Often confused with cultists, misguided heretics, or crazed fanatics,
|CK0the Priests of Set dedicate their lives to a ambitious pursuit of
|CK0power. They gain this power through a series of bargains with Set,
|CK0the god of Chaos. These priests are terrifying in combat, mixing
|CK0heavy-hitting blows with the divine dominance of their god.
|CK0
|CK0Priests typcially opt for scale or banded armor, forgoing full plate
|CK0for the rush of battle. For weapons, priests vary from dual-wielding
|CK0daggers to large blunt polearms.
|CK0
|CK0The guild has two main abilities that all initiates learn: Bolt and
|CK0Mend. Bolt sacrifices some of the caster's own vitality to Set,
|CK0which is rewarded with a devastating attack on a foe. Similarly,
|CK0Mend uses some of the caster's vitality to restore health over time
|CK0for a target.
|CK0
|CK0Trained priests learn other divine abilities, several of which
|CK0empower Bolt and Mend. Priests value wisdom over all attributes so
|CK0that they can strengthen their connection with Set. They also focus
|CK0on charisma to get their way and to guide others, and constitution
|CK0so that they can make more powerful bargains.
